w you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"a1.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"a1.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"a2.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"a2.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"a3.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"a3.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"df_united.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"df_united.rds\"\n    },\n    \"exclusion.bed\": {\n      \"_file\": \"exclusion.bed\"\n    },\n    \"mk_db\": {\n      \"a1.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"a1.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"a1.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"a1.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"a2.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"a2.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"a2.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"a2.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"a3.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"a3.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"a3.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"a3.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/snv_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_4VIBCcaJanW7xYou9NIhpD6v", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files: `df_united.rds` and `exclusion.bed`.\\n2. Convert the `start` column in `exclusion.bed` to 1-based by adding 1.\\n3. Perform an anti-join between the methylKit tibble and the BED file.\\n4. Save the filtered tibble to `output/df_united_excl.rds`.\\n5. Calculate the number of sites in the original and filtered tibbles.\\n6. Write the summary TSV `output/snv_stats.tsv` with columns `dataset, n_sites` and rows `united` /